This parent of both New England Savings Bank and OmniBank of Connecticut named Seymour M. Smith senior vice president and chief financial officer.
The 48-year-old Mr. Smith formerly was president of Wellington Forest Inc., an Essex, Conn., real estate investment and development company.
He succeeds Floyd Champagne, who left the bank.
Mr. Champagne had held the title of senior vice president of investments. 

